# Trinity Protocol Evolution Plan

This plan outlines the steps to implement the improvements proposed in the Trinity Protocol Roadmap.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This plan introduces a centralized `trinity` CLI and `Makefile` which will become the standard entry points for all project repositories. This will change the workflow for autonomous agents.


## Proposed Changes

### Documentation & Governance

#### [MODIFY] [GEMINI.md](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/GEMINI.md)
- Populate with the Project Constitution (Trinity Protocol Ecosystem Q&A).
- Establish as the primary reference for system behavior.


### Unification (Launch Mechanism)

#### [NEW] [Makefile](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/Makefile)
- Define standard targets: `train`, `predict`, `validate`, `clean`.
- Abstract environment setup and dependency execution.


#### [NEW] [trinity.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/scripts/trinity.py)
- A CLI tool to act as a single entry point.
- Usage: `python scripts/trinity.py <task> <parameters>`.


#### [NEW] [manifest.json](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/manifest.json)
- Declarative metadata for the project (version, scripts, data dependencies).


### Hardening (ProcessGuard)

#### [NEW] [process_guard.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/scripts/process_guard.py)
- Real-time performance monitoring.
- Integration with ensembling scripts to prevent poor model merging.


## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `make validate` to run JudgeGuard and ProcessGuard checks.
- Smoke tests for the CLI tool.


### Manual Verification
- Verify that `trinity train` correctly invokes the appropriate training script.
- Check [GEMINI.md](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/GEMINI.md) for readability and accuracy.
